</li><li class="postbit blockbody" id="post_8">
	<div class="header">
		<div class="datetime">June 29th, 2013, 03:32 AM</div>
		<span class="username">MI Redeux</span>
	</div>
	
	
		<div class="title">Re: How do you store your backups?</div>
	
	<div class="content">
		<blockquote class="restore">I have been trying out an Airport Time Capsule for the past week or so.  It is /okay/, however I am not a big fan of it if you can manage your own router + nas readily.  The router portion of the time capsule is especially poor as it offers little in the way of configuration.  The only good thing I have to say about it really is that it has 802.11ac instead of just 802.11n.  I would much rather get that in a less restrictive router though. If you absolutely must have an Airport Time Capsule, use it in bridge mode and have a more configurable router elsewhere.  It is one of the worser Apple devices I've tried out. If you have no idea what you are doing when it comes to networking or you are especially disinterested in spending any time dicking around with such it may be for you, otherwise I would avoid it even if you are pretty integrated with Apple's ecosystem (like me).</blockquote>
	</div>
